EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to criminal procedure; revising provisions relating
to vacating a judgment of conviction and sealing certain
records of certain victims; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes certain victims convicted of certain offenses to petition
2 the court to vacate a judgment of conviction against the victim and seal all
3 documents relating to the case. Under existing law, such offenses include: (1) any
4 crime under the laws of this State, other than a crime of violence; or (2) a violation
5 of a county, city or town ordinance for loitering for the purposes of solicitation or
6 prostitution. (NRS 179.247) Section 1 of this bill: (1) expands the list of offenses
7 under which a victim of human trafficking may petition the court to vacate a
8 judgment of conviction and seal all documents relating to the case to include any
9 crime under the laws of this State and any violation of a county, city or town
10 ordinance; and (2) revises the applicable criminal procedure. Section 3 of this bill
11 provides that the changes in section 1 apply: (1) retroactively to any conviction
12 obtained before the effective date of this bill; (2) to any conviction obtained on or
13 after the effective date of this bill; and (3) to a petition filed on or after the effective
14 date of this bill.
